JIT compiles hot paths to native code. Profile-guided: interpret first, then compile methods called >10k times.

Java I/O evolved from blocking streams to NIO channels and the modern Files API.

```java
// Modern Files API (Java 11+) — preferred
Path path = Path.of("/data/input.txt");
String content = Files.readString(path);
List<String> lines = Files.readAllLines(path);
Files.writeString(Path.of("out.txt"), content);

// Buffered streams for large files
try (var reader = new BufferedReader(
       new FileReader("large.csv"))) {
  String line;
  while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null)
    process(line);
}

// NIO2: walk directory tree
Files.walk(Path.of("/src"))
  .filter(p -> p.toString().endsWith(".java"))
  .forEach(System.out::println);

// Serialization
class User implements Serializable {
  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;
  String name; transient String password; // transient = skip
}
// Write
try (var oos = new ObjectOutputStream(
       new FileOutputStream("user.ser"))) {
  oos.writeObject(new User("Alice"));
}
```
Prefer JSON serialization (Jackson/Gson) over Java serialization for cross-system data exchange.

These patterns appear constantly in Java interviews — knowing them cold is mandatory.

```java
// equals + hashCode contract: equal objects must have equal hashes
class Point {
  final int x, y;
  Point(int x, int y) { this.x = x; this.y = y; }

  @Override public boolean equals(Object o) {
    if (this == o) return true;
    if (!(o instanceof Point p)) return false;
    return x == p.x && y == p.y;
  }
  @Override public int hashCode() {
    return Objects.hash(x, y);
  }
}

// Comparable for natural ordering
class Employee implements Comparable<Employee> {
  String name; double salary;
  public int compareTo(Employee other) {
    return Double.compare(this.salary, other.salary);
  }
}
list.sort(Comparator.comparing(Employee::getName)
  .thenComparingDouble(Employee::getSalary).reversed());

// Immutable class recipe
final class Money {
  private final long cents;
  private final String currency;
  Money(long cents, String currency) {
    this.cents = cents;
    this.currency = Objects.requireNonNull(currency);
  }
  Money add(Money other) { return new Money(cents+other.cents, currency); }
}

// Builder pattern
class Config { /* use Lombok @Builder or implement manually */ }
